Metadata-Version: 2.1
Name: LAT-dwarfs
Version: 1.0
Summary: Python code to derive data-driven upper limits on the thermally averaged, velocity-weighted pair-annihilation cross-section (velocity-independent) of a user-defined particle dark matter model using the expected differential gamma-ray spectrum of an annihilation event (provided by the user) as well as 10 years of Fermi-LAT data from observations of the Milky WayÂ´s dwarf spheroidal galaxies.
Author: Francesca Calore, Pasquale Serpico, Bryan Zaldivar
Author-email: calore@lapth.cnrs.fr, serpico@lapth.cnrs.fr, b.zaldivar.m@csic.es
